{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567105","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567105"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:52+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:52+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18933"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18933","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18933"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.8,0.06,0.08,0.01,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11667"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80345"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11667","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11667"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18933"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65614"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2425"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5669"},{"type":"tags","id":"5671"},{"type":"tags","id":"5770"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11333"},{"type":"tags","id":"11380"},{"type":"tags","id":"11382"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27453"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27456"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80345","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80345"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student is observing a gynaecological procedure. After the patient is under general anaesthetic, the surgeon offers to let the student perform a speculum examination for learning purposes. The patient was not informed about this possibility during the consent process.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate response from the medical student?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decline and explain that specific consent was not obtained","Accept the offer as this is a teaching hospital","Accept the offer as the patient is already consented for the procedure","Ask the anaesthetist if it would be acceptable","Seek permission from the patient\u0027s next of kin"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct response is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edecline and explain that specific consent was not obtained\u003C/strong\u003E. Performing an examination without explicit prior consent is unethical and potentially illegal, even in an educational context. The patient must be informed and give consent while conscious and capable of making an autonomous decision.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect responses are inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAccept the offer as this is a teaching hospital\u003C/strong\u003E - Being in a teaching hospital does not override the requirement for specific informed consent for educational examinations\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAccept the offer as the patient is already consented for the procedure\u003C/strong\u003E - Consent for the primary procedure does not extend to additional examinations for educational purposes\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAsk the anaesthetist if it would be acceptable\u003C/strong\u003E - The anaesthetist cannot provide proxy consent for the patient\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESeek permission from the patient\u0027s next of kin\u003C/strong\u003E - Next of kin cannot provide consent for non-therapeutic procedures when the patient had capacity to consent beforehand\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis scenario highlights the importance of obtaining specific informed consent for any examination or procedure, particularly those performed primarily for educational purposes. The patient\u0027s right to autonomy must be respected at all times.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Valid informed consent must be obtained before any examination or procedure, even if the patient will be under general anaesthetic.","Consent must be obtained while the patient is conscious and able to make an informed decision.","Students must not perform examinations solely for educational purposes without explicit prior consent from the patient."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","AMSA Code of Ethics. In Australian medical student association [online]. Available at: https://amsa.org.au/advocacy-and-policy/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65614"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18933"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65614","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65614"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T14:19:35+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T14:20:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11667"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80345"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tag